WEBVTT

00:06.800 --> 00:09.000
( theme music playing )

00:14.000 --> 00:17.167
Larry:
AUNTIE RAE, AUNTIE RAE?

00:17.200 --> 00:20.633
- YOU NEED SOMETHING?
- I WANT YOU TO COME WITH ME.
I WANT TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

00:20.667 --> 00:22.133
OH, ALL RIGHT THEN.
WHAT IS IT?

00:22.167 --> 00:24.267
EH, DON'T WORRY.
JUST COME WITH ME.

00:24.300 --> 00:27.567
YOU KNOW,
YOU SAID HOW MUCH
YOU LOVE GARDENING,

00:27.600 --> 00:29.733
AND HOW YOU WISH YOU
COULD GARDEN HERE,

00:29.767 --> 00:33.133
SO I CLEARED THIS
LITTLE AREA FOR YOU.

00:33.167 --> 00:34.533
- AND... THERE YOU GO.
- LARRY.

00:34.567 --> 00:36.300
YOU DID THIS FOR ME?

00:36.333 --> 00:38.633
- I DID IT FOR YOU!
- OH, LARRY!

00:38.667 --> 00:40.567
- HUH?
- OH-HO! LARRY!

00:40.600 --> 00:43.133
GROW SOME LETTUCE, AUNTIE RAE.
GROW SOME LETTUCE!

00:43.167 --> 00:46.067
YOU DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH
I APPRECIATE THIS.

00:46.100 --> 00:48.633
YOU'VE BEEN SO GOOD
TO US, LARRY,

00:48.667 --> 00:51.467
MY FAMILY.
I REALLY APPRECIATE IT.

00:51.500 --> 00:53.467
I REALLY
APPRECIATE IT, LARRY!

00:53.500 --> 00:55.833
THANK YOU, LARRY.
I--

00:58.567 --> 01:02.133
LARRY,
YOU'RE DISGUSTING.

01:02.167 --> 01:03.733
AH!

01:03.767 --> 01:06.067
AGH!
AUNTIE RAE!

01:07.633 --> 01:09.467
( sighs )

01:09.500 --> 01:12.467
Larry:
SHE CALLED ME DISGUSTING.
( laughs )

01:12.500 --> 01:14.500
OH MY GOD.

01:15.933 --> 01:19.100
- WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?
- AND SHE RAN INTO THE HOUSE.

01:19.133 --> 01:21.067
- OH MY GOD.
- HOW DOES THAT HAPPEN TO YOU?

01:21.067 --> 01:24.067
YOU KNOW, SHE WENT
OVER THE APPROPRIATE
AMOUNT OF TIME

01:24.067 --> 01:27.067
THAT I CAN HAVE
HUMAN CONTACT
WITHOUT GETTING AROUSED.

01:27.100 --> 01:29.100
I ONLY HAVE FIVE SECONDS.

01:29.133 --> 01:31.167
AFTER THAT, IT'S OUT
OF MY CONTROL.

01:31.200 --> 01:34.433
NOT ME. I'VE GOT
DISCIPLINE DOWN THERE.
I HAVE A VERY DISCERNING PENIS.

01:34.467 --> 01:35.800
- NO...
- VERY DISCERNING.

01:35.833 --> 01:38.067
- MY PENIS IS AN ANIMAL.
- REALLY, JUST OUT OF CONTROL?

01:38.067 --> 01:40.367
- IT'S A FERAL TIGER, YEAH.
- IT'S WILD.

01:40.400 --> 01:42.933
OH, SO HOW'D YOUR--
HOW'D THE APPOINTMENT GO?
WITH THE DOCTOR?

01:42.967 --> 01:44.633
GREAT.

01:44.667 --> 01:47.400
HE'S GONNA SNIP-SNIP,
AND...

01:47.433 --> 01:49.700
I WILL NO LONGER
BE SNORING.

01:49.733 --> 01:51.800
- REALLY?
- GOING IN ON
THURSDAY MORNING.

01:51.833 --> 01:53.633
- FANTASTIC.
- UNBELIEVABLE!

01:53.667 --> 01:56.233
- FANTASTIC.
- MY DOG HOWLS

01:56.267 --> 01:58.400
FROM MY SNORING.
I WAKE UP MY DOG.

01:58.433 --> 02:00.900
MY DOG STARTS HOWLING.
I'M OUT OF CONTROL.

02:00.933 --> 02:02.700
- THIS'LL BE GOOD.
- THIS'LL BE GREAT.

02:02.733 --> 02:04.233
- IT'S ABOUT TIME.
- IT IS ABOUT TIME.

02:04.267 --> 02:05.933
- YEAH.
- IT'S ABOUT TIME.

02:05.967 --> 02:09.533
HEY, GUESS WHAT ELSE?
I THINK BEN STILLER'S GONNA
COME WITH ME AS A CLIENT.

02:09.567 --> 02:11.367
- ARE YOU KIDDING?
- NO!

02:11.400 --> 02:14.400
- HAVE YOU MET WITH HIM?
- NO, I'M MEETING WITH HIM
THIS WEEK.

02:14.433 --> 02:17.967
- IF YOU COULD SIGN HIM...
- I THINK IT'S A SLAM-DUNK.
DONE DEAL.

02:18.067 --> 02:19.800
IT'S GONNA BRING YOU IN
SO MUCH INCOME.

02:19.833 --> 02:21.133
- HUGE INCOME, I KNOW.
- MY GOD.

02:21.167 --> 02:22.933
- THAT'S AMAZING.
- HELLO.

02:22.967 --> 02:24.533
- HI.
- I KNOW YOU
COULDN'T DECIDE

02:24.567 --> 02:27.067
BETWEEN THE SLAW AND THE SOUP,
SO I BROUGHT YOU BOTH.

02:27.067 --> 02:29.333
WOW, THANK YOU
SO VERY MUCH.

02:29.367 --> 02:31.900
AND HERE'S YOUR SANDWICH.
CAN I GET YOU SOMETHING
TO DRINK?

02:31.933 --> 02:33.833
YOU KNOW WHAT I'D LOVE?
I'D LOVE AN ARNOLD PALMER.

02:33.867 --> 02:36.167
- OKAY, I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
- THANK YOU.

02:36.200 --> 02:39.067
EXCUSE ME?
CAN I GIVE YOU
A DRINK ORDER?

02:39.067 --> 02:41.567
- SURE.
- I'LL JUST HAVE
AN ICED TEA.

02:41.600 --> 02:44.567
- AN ICED TEA. OKAY.
ARNOLD PALMER... OF COURSE.
- THANKS AGAIN.

02:44.600 --> 02:47.633
THANK YOU.
MAN, SHE'S NICE.

02:47.667 --> 02:50.467
YEAH. NICE TO PEOPLE
WITH HAIR, SHE'S NICE.

02:50.500 --> 02:53.533
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
- WHAT AM I TALKING ABOUT?

02:53.567 --> 02:56.467
- YEAH.
- BALD PEOPLE GET DISCRIMINATED
AGAINST CONSTANTLY.

02:56.500 --> 02:58.433
AND YOU JUST SAW
A PERFECT EXAMPLE OF IT.

02:58.467 --> 03:00.333
OH, IT'S BECAUSE
YOU'RE BALD.

03:00.367 --> 03:02.567
YEAH, ASK ANY BALD PERSON.
ASK, GO AHEAD.

03:02.600 --> 03:04.433
YOU STILL HAVE ISSUES
WITH BEING BALD.

03:04.467 --> 03:07.767
YOU KNOW, IF I WERE BALD--
IF I WOKE UP TOMORROW
AND I FOUND MYSELF BALD,

03:07.800 --> 03:10.733
I'D BE SO COOL WITH IT.
IT'D BE NO BIG DEAL.
IT'S ALL NATURAL.

03:10.767 --> 03:13.067
- YEAH, RIGHT,
THAT'S WHAT EVERYBODY SAYS.
- WHATEVER.

03:13.067 --> 03:15.167
HEY, THEY HAVE
A PHARMACY HERE, RIGHT?

03:15.200 --> 03:17.367
- YEAH.
- I GOTTA GET
A PRESCRIPTION FILLED.

03:17.400 --> 03:19.100
I'M GONNA GO NOW,
DROP IT OFF,

03:19.133 --> 03:21.133
THEN I'LL PICK IT UP
WHEN I'M DONE.

03:21.167 --> 03:22.933
BEAUTIFUL.

03:34.567 --> 03:36.800
- HI.
- OH, HI THERE.

03:37.900 --> 03:40.167
AH, LET'S TAKE
A LOOK HERE.

03:40.200 --> 03:41.567
CAN I GET THAT IN
THE NEXT HALF HOUR?

03:41.600 --> 03:43.100
SURE. YEAH,
WE CAN DO THAT.

03:43.133 --> 03:44.700
GREAT, THANK YOU.

03:47.233 --> 03:49.100
- Larry: THAT'S ODD.
- Jeff: WHAT?

03:49.133 --> 03:51.400
I COULD HAVE SWORN
WHEN I LEFT,

03:51.433 --> 03:54.267
I HAD ABOUT TWICE
AS MANY FRENCH FRIES

03:54.300 --> 03:56.767
- AS THERE ARE NOW.
- HM.

03:56.800 --> 03:59.700
- YOU WOULDN'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT THIS, WOULD YOU?
- NO IDEA.

03:59.733 --> 04:01.067
- HUH?
- NO IDEA.

04:01.100 --> 04:02.900
- NO IDEA?
- NO.

04:08.400 --> 04:11.267
- NO IDEA?
- I TOLD YOU I HAD NO IDEA!
WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?

04:11.300 --> 04:14.467
- JUST EAT.
- MAYBE SOMEBODY COULD SHED
SOME LIGHT ON THIS FOR US.

04:14.500 --> 04:17.367
EXCUSE ME. HI,
I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU.

04:17.400 --> 04:21.067
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.
- I'M WONDERING IF YOU
NOTICED ANYTHING UNUSUAL

04:21.067 --> 04:23.400
GOING ON AT THIS TABLE
AFTER I LEFT?

04:23.433 --> 04:26.633
WELL, I--
I REALLY COULDN'T SAY.
I DON'T WANT

04:26.667 --> 04:28.467
TO IMPINGE
ON A FRIENDSHIP.

04:28.500 --> 04:31.067
IMPINGE AWAY.
GO AHEAD AND IMPINGE.

04:31.067 --> 04:33.400
I TOOK ONE.
SHOOT ME.

04:33.433 --> 04:36.067
ONE.
TWO OF THEM MIGHT HAVE
BEEN STUCK TOGETHER.

04:36.067 --> 04:37.933
MM-MM-MM.
THANK YOU.

04:37.967 --> 04:40.433
- ARE YOU A DOCTOR?
- YES, DR. FLOMM.

04:40.467 --> 04:42.933
- I'M AN ORTHOPEDIST.
- REALLY? AN ORTHOPEDIST?

04:42.967 --> 04:44.367
- MM-HM.
- HI, MY NAME'S LARRY.

04:44.400 --> 04:46.867
HI, LARRY.
I'M-- I'M SHEILA.

04:46.900 --> 04:49.867
NICE TO MEET YOU.
SO YOU WORK IN THE BUILDING?

04:52.200 --> 04:54.200
Leon:
GOD DAMN, LARRY.
WHAT THE FUCK, MAN?

04:54.233 --> 04:56.467
YOU HUG MY AUNTIE, MAN,
YOU STAB HER
IN THE STOMACH?

04:56.500 --> 04:58.367
- OH WELL...
- WHAT THE FUCK WAS THAT?

04:58.400 --> 05:01.067
SHE HUGGED ME
AND SHE HELD THAT HUG
FOR OVER FIVE SECONDS.

05:01.067 --> 05:03.300
- WHAT THE FUCK?
- I HAVE NO CONTROL
AFTER FIVE SECONDS.

05:03.333 --> 05:05.233
- SO YOU GOT
A FIVE-SECOND RULE?
- NOT A RULE,

05:05.267 --> 05:08.600
IT'S AN APPROXIMATE AMOUNT
OF TIME THAT IT'S GONNA TAKE
FOR SOMETHING TO HAPPEN.

05:08.633 --> 05:10.800
WHAT THE FUCK,
I MEAN, WHAT THE FUCK?
LORETTA.

05:10.833 --> 05:12.167
- OH, I'M SORRY.
- L.D.?

05:12.200 --> 05:14.133
- WHAT?
- YOU HAVE LOST YOUR
DAMN MIND.

05:14.167 --> 05:15.733
- NO, I...
- AUNTIE RAE?

05:15.767 --> 05:18.333
I CAN'T CONTROL IT.
I HAVE NO CONTROL.
IT'S NOT MY FAULT.

05:18.367 --> 05:20.133
JUST LIKE THAT,
YOU GOT TURNED ON?

05:20.167 --> 05:22.333
NOT JUST LIKE THAT.
THAT'S A LONG TIME,
FIVE SECONDS.

05:22.367 --> 05:25.233
HE GOT A FIVE-SECOND RULE.
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE--
BOING, IT COME OUT.

05:25.267 --> 05:28.333
- WHERE'S YOUR "MISSISSIPPI"?
YOU GOTTA PUT MISSISSIPPI IN.
- Both: MISSISSIPPI?

05:28.367 --> 05:30.833
THAT'S HOW YOU COUNT--
"ONE-MISSISSIPPI,
TWO-MISSISSIPPI,

05:30.867 --> 05:33.467
THREE-MISSISSIPPI,
FOUR-MISSISSIPPI,
FIVE-MISSISSIPPI."

05:33.500 --> 05:35.100
- THAT'S WAY TOO LONG.
- WAY TOO LONG.

05:35.133 --> 05:37.200
- YOU'RE STRETCHING IT OUT FOR--
- I'M NOT STRETCHING IT OUT.

05:37.233 --> 05:39.333
- I SHORTENED IT.
- I'M JUST SAYIN',
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME

05:39.367 --> 05:41.367
- SINCE MY UNCLE
PASSED AWAY, MAN.
- THAT'S RIGHT.

05:41.400 --> 05:43.567
YOU ALL OVER HER.
YOU STAB HER IN THE FUCKIN'
STOMACH, MAN.

05:43.600 --> 05:45.367
BELIEVE ME, IT'S NOT
GONNA HAPPEN AGAIN.

05:45.400 --> 05:47.667
YOU BETTER MAKE SURE
IT DON'T HAPPEN AGAIN,
BECAUSE WE CAN GO.

05:47.700 --> 05:49.267
- WE CAN GO, MAN.
- WE CAN GO. WE CAN
GO ANYWHERE.

05:49.300 --> 05:52.100
- WHERE YOU GONNA GO?
- ANYWHERE. GET OUT
OF HERE, I KNOW THAT.

05:52.133 --> 05:54.067
- Leon: WE GOT PLACES TO GO.
- YOU KNOW, IT'S JUST

05:54.100 --> 05:56.067
I'M SO STARVED FOR AFFECTION,
I GUESS THAT

05:56.067 --> 05:58.867
- ANY KIND OF CONTACT...
- TALK TO YOUR MAN.

05:58.900 --> 06:02.367
- YOU GOT ONE MORE CHANCE, L.D.
- I JUST MET A DOCTOR, ACTUALLY.

06:02.400 --> 06:04.467
I'M GONNA GO CALL HER
FOR A DATE RIGHT NOW.

06:04.500 --> 06:06.800
- SHE'S VERY ATTRACTIVE.
- HANDLE YOUR BUSINESS.

06:06.833 --> 06:09.267
- BUT NO-- NO MORE
HUGGING, DON'T WORRY.
- OH PLEASE, PLEASE DON'T.

06:09.300 --> 06:11.367
CALL THAT GODDAMN DOCTOR,
GET A DIAGNOSIS,

06:11.400 --> 06:13.800
AND-AND-AND-- AND GO
STAB SOMEBODY ELSE, MAN.

06:13.833 --> 06:17.067
Dr. Flomm:
AND WHAT HAPPENS WHEN YOU--
WHEN YOU TURN YOUR PALM?

06:17.100 --> 06:19.167
- YEAH, IT HURTS.
- WORSE, OKAY.

06:19.200 --> 06:21.267
- ( phone rings )
- JUST A MOMENT, PLEASE.

06:21.300 --> 06:24.067
- HELLO, DR. FLOMM.
- OH, DR. FLOMM.

06:24.100 --> 06:27.200
- THIS IS LARRY DAVID CALLING.
- Oh hi, Larry.
How are you?

06:27.233 --> 06:30.133
- GOOD, I MET YOU
EARLIER IN THE CAFETERIA.
- Yes yes, I remember.

06:30.167 --> 06:33.733
- WOULD YOU LIKE
TO MAKE AN APPOINTMENT?
- UH, NO, ACTUALLY.

06:33.767 --> 06:36.167
I'M CALLING FOR,
UM, A DATE.

06:36.200 --> 06:38.200
OH I SEE.
WELL, I'M WITH
A PATIENT RIGHT NOW.

06:38.233 --> 06:39.867
Oh Jeez,
I'm so sorry.

06:39.900 --> 06:42.633
OKAY, IS-- IS TONIGHT
GOOD FOR YOU?

06:42.667 --> 06:45.300
ACTUALLY I'M ALL
BOOKED UP TONIGHT, BUT I
AM AVAILABLE TOMORROW

06:45.333 --> 06:47.200
BETWEEN 5:00 AND 6:00
OR ANYTIME AFTER 8:30.

06:47.233 --> 06:49.300
- OKAY, I'LL TAKE THE 8:30.
- Terrific.

06:49.333 --> 06:51.433
SPEAK TO MY RECEPTIONIST
TO GET THE PERTINENT DETAILS.

06:51.467 --> 06:53.867
- I'LL CALL YOUR RECEPTIONIST.
- IF YOU NEED TO CANCEL

06:53.900 --> 06:55.800
OR IN CASE OF ANY EMERGENCY,
JUST PAGE ME.

06:55.833 --> 06:57.167
Okay.
Okay, will do.

06:57.200 --> 06:59.433
GOOD, AND I RECOMMEND
BEING FIVE MINUTES EARLY.

06:59.467 --> 07:00.767
Okay, I'll see you
tomorrow.

07:00.800 --> 07:02.267
All right, Larry,Thank you.

07:02.300 --> 07:04.500
- OKAY.
- ( clicks )

07:10.467 --> 07:12.133
HI.

07:12.167 --> 07:14.167
IS... SHEILA HERE?

07:14.200 --> 07:16.400
YEAH, COME ON IN.
I'M HER SISTER.

07:16.433 --> 07:18.133
- OH, HI.
- YOU MUST BE LARRY.

07:18.167 --> 07:20.067
- YEAH.
- JUST COME ON IN,
HAVE A SEAT.

07:20.100 --> 07:22.067
- MAKE YOURSELF AT HOME.
- OH, THANKS.

07:22.100 --> 07:24.967
- SHE'LL BE RIGHT DOWN.
- ( soft jazz playing )

07:46.200 --> 07:48.533
YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT.
IT'LL BE FINE.

07:48.567 --> 07:50.300
- THANKS, SHEILA.
- OH HI, LARRY.

07:50.333 --> 07:52.300
- HI HI.
- THIS IS MY BROTHER JOE.

07:52.333 --> 07:54.067
- LARRY DAVID.
- HI, JOE.

07:54.067 --> 07:56.300
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- I SUPPOSE YOU MET TRISH,
MY SISTER.

07:56.333 --> 07:57.567
YES, YEAH.

07:57.600 --> 07:59.400
- WOW.
- HUH?

07:59.433 --> 08:01.933
- YOU LOOK GREAT.
- IT TOOK ME ABOUT
TWO HOURS TO GET READY.

08:03.400 --> 08:05.733
YOUR BROTHER AND SISTER,
THEY'RE STAYING WITH YOU?

08:05.767 --> 08:08.867
YEAH, THEY'RE GONNA BE
WITH ME JUST A COUPLE MONTHS.

08:08.900 --> 08:11.133
- SO...
- YOU KNOW, I'VE GOT PEOPLE
IN MY HOUSE TOO.

08:11.167 --> 08:12.733
- YOU'RE KIDDING.
- NO.

08:12.767 --> 08:15.267
YOU KNOW, IT'S GREAT
AND THEN SOMETIMES
IT'S NOT SO GREAT.

08:15.300 --> 08:17.167
WELL, I TOOK IN
A HOMELESS FAMILY...

08:17.200 --> 08:19.567
- YOU WHAT?
- ...FROM-- FROM--
FROM THE HURRICANE.

08:19.600 --> 08:20.700
- YOU'RE KIDDING.
- NO.

08:20.733 --> 08:22.833
ANYWAY, THEIR--
THEIR NAME IS "BLACK."

08:22.867 --> 08:25.100
- UH-HUH.
- AND-- AND THEY'RE
ACTUALLY BLACK.

08:25.133 --> 08:27.767
- WELL, THAT MAKES IT EASY.
- EXACTLY, YEAH.

08:27.800 --> 08:29.100
YEAH.

08:29.133 --> 08:31.067
- CAN I MOVE ON?
- ABSOLUTELY.

08:31.067 --> 08:33.233
HUH? ALL RIGHT,
I GOT A GROIN ISSUE.

08:33.267 --> 08:35.067
- OH, OKAY.
- I-- I PULLED IT.

08:35.067 --> 08:37.067
DID YOU ICE IT RIGHT AWAY?

08:37.067 --> 08:38.967
- NO.
- OKAY, SO PUT A LITTLE
BIT OF HEAT

08:39.067 --> 08:40.667
- ON THE GROIN...
- HEAT ON THE GROIN.

08:40.700 --> 08:43.133
- ...AND THEN I'D MASSAGE IT.
- YOU WANT ME TO MASSAGE IT?

08:43.167 --> 08:44.633
- OH ABSOLUTELY.
- REALLY?

08:44.667 --> 08:46.500
YOU NEVER WANT
TO MASSAGE WITH MUSCLE,

08:46.533 --> 08:49.067
- YOU ALWAYS WANT
TO MASSAGE LATERALLY.
- LATERAL, OKAY.

08:49.100 --> 08:52.300
FOR INSTANCE,
THIS IS YOUR GROIN.
JUST-- YOU JUST MASSAGE ACROSS.

08:52.333 --> 08:55.100
WATCH OUT FOR MY TESTICLES
RIGHT OVER THERE.

08:55.133 --> 08:57.233
( Dr. Flomm laughing )

09:00.600 --> 09:02.767
LARRY?

09:04.533 --> 09:07.433
WHY DON'T WE MOVE THIS
TO MY BEDROOM?

09:08.700 --> 09:10.167
SURE.

09:10.200 --> 09:12.667
GO UPSTAIRS,
TAKE OFF YOUR CLOTHES,

09:12.700 --> 09:15.133
AND I'LL BE IN TO SEE
YOU IN A FEW MINUTES.

09:17.833 --> 09:19.367
OKAY.

09:25.267 --> 09:27.767
( exhales )

09:27.800 --> 09:31.067
( light jazz playing )

09:43.400 --> 09:45.567
LARRY?

09:45.600 --> 09:47.100
- HEY.
- HI.

09:47.133 --> 09:49.100
UH, LISTEN, I--
I AM SO SORRY.

09:49.133 --> 09:50.900
I-- I HATE
TO TELL YOU THIS,

09:50.933 --> 09:52.933
BUT MY BROTHER
AND SISTER JUST
CAME BACK.

09:52.967 --> 09:54.933
- THEY WEREN'T SUPPOSED
TO BE HERE.
- OH.

09:54.967 --> 09:57.700
AND MY BROTHER GOT
FOOD POISONING, SO THEY
CAME BACK EARLY,

09:57.733 --> 10:00.100
AND I--
I'M REALLY SORRY.

10:00.133 --> 10:02.233
- WELL, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?
- SO...

10:02.267 --> 10:04.467
- IT HAPPENS.
- ...WE NEED TO RESCHEDULE.

10:04.500 --> 10:07.267
WHY DON'T YOU GET DRESSED
AND I'LL MEET YOU
IN THE FOYER?

10:16.667 --> 10:18.367
I'M TELLING YOU, JEFFREY,

10:18.400 --> 10:20.500
THERE'S NOTHING
LIKE DATING A DOCTOR.

10:20.533 --> 10:24.033
WE TALKED FOR 45 MINUTES
ABOUT MY GROIN INJURY.

10:24.067 --> 10:27.133
NO NO, SHE JUST
WANTS ME TO MASSAGE IT.

10:27.167 --> 10:29.300
IT'S KILLING ME TOO.

10:29.333 --> 10:31.700
UM, SO LISTEN--

10:31.733 --> 10:34.800
I'M GONNA SEE YOU LATER.
I'M GONNA STOP BY BEFORE
YOUR OPERATION.

10:34.833 --> 10:36.600
OKAY, MAN.

10:36.633 --> 10:38.667
OKAY, TAKE CARE.

10:44.900 --> 10:46.467
( groans )

10:46.500 --> 10:48.367
( gasps )

10:49.400 --> 10:51.233
( screams )

10:53.267 --> 10:55.833
OH!
AUNTIE RAE!

10:58.200 --> 10:59.867
- Larry: YOU KNOW WHAT?
- WHAT?

10:59.900 --> 11:02.500
- LAST NIGHT, I KNOW
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.
- YEAH?

11:02.533 --> 11:04.700
- THIS THING, YOU KNOW.
- OH, THAT THING.

11:04.733 --> 11:07.633
- AND BELIEVE ME, I RESPECT
YOUR MEDICAL JUDGMENT.
- MM-HM?

11:07.667 --> 11:10.700
- I THINK IT'S CANCER.
- ( laughs ) IT'S NOT CANCER.

11:10.733 --> 11:13.100
HUH? I'VE NEVER
HAD CANCER BEFORE
BUT I'M IMAGINING

11:13.133 --> 11:14.967
- THIS IS HOW IT FEELS LIKE.
- HOW WOULD YOU KNOW?

11:15.067 --> 11:16.733
NO NO, IT'S NOT.

11:16.767 --> 11:18.800
( clears throat )
I'M GONNA...

11:18.833 --> 11:20.633
HEAD TO THE MEN'S ROOM.

11:20.667 --> 11:22.533
I-- OKAY, THAT'S FINE.

11:22.567 --> 11:24.967
I JUST... I'M A LITTLE
SHY ABOUT THIS,

11:25.067 --> 11:27.800
AND I JUST HAVE--
I JUST WROTE YOU
