TOGETHER FRIDAY NIGHT

21:19.833 --> 21:22.333
- AT THE BEL-AIR
REGENCY HOTEL..."
- WHAT?

21:22.367 --> 21:24.567
"...JUST THE TWO OF US."

21:24.600 --> 21:27.533
- ( sighs )
- "SO TIRED OF ALL THESE

21:27.567 --> 21:29.833
BROTHERS AND SISTERS
AROUND.

21:29.867 --> 21:33.067
I KNOW YOU FEEL
THE SAME WAY.

21:33.100 --> 21:35.633
TELL ME YOUR LIFE
WOULDN'T BE BETTER

21:35.667 --> 21:38.467
WITHOUT THE BLACKS."

21:38.500 --> 21:40.067
HUH?

21:41.500 --> 21:44.067
OH, OKAY, UH...
NO NO NO NO NO.

21:44.067 --> 21:46.333
Pharmacist: IT'S YOUR BUSINESS.

21:46.367 --> 21:48.500
- YOU'RE MISINTERPRETING IT.
- HERE'S YOUR PRESCRIPTION.

21:48.533 --> 21:50.767
- NO, SEE I'VE GOT--
- TAKE YOUR PRESCRIPTION.

21:50.800 --> 21:53.133
- THANK YOU.
- I'VE GOT PEOPLE
IN MY HOUSE.

21:53.167 --> 21:55.500
THERE'S...

21:55.533 --> 21:58.200
THEY'RE BLACK BUT
THEIR NAME IS BLACK!

21:58.233 --> 22:00.833
SHE'S GOT...

22:00.867 --> 22:03.433
HER BROTHERS
AND SISTERS.

22:14.767 --> 22:17.600
( soft piano playing )

22:25.800 --> 22:28.067
Dr. Flomm:
IT'S OPEN.
COME ON IN.

22:29.467 --> 22:33.067
HI. YOU HAVE GOT
THE WORST HANDWRITING...

22:33.100 --> 22:34.800
- ( laughs )
- ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?

22:34.833 --> 22:37.067
- NO? YOU COULDN'T READ IT?
- YOU EXPECT ANYBODY TO--

22:37.067 --> 22:39.167
- COULDN'T READ IT?
I GAVE IT TO 10,000--
- OH!

22:39.200 --> 22:41.633
- A PHARMACIST,
A PHARMACIST WOUND UP...
- I'M SO SORRY.

22:41.667 --> 22:44.367
- ...TRANSLATING THAT FOR ME.
- OH, I'M SORRY.

22:49.433 --> 22:50.633
MM.

23:11.933 --> 23:13.967
Larry:
THANKS FOR DRIVING ME HOME.

23:14.067 --> 23:15.467
REALLY, I--
I COULDN'T DRIVE.

23:15.500 --> 23:17.200
I JUST DON'T--
I DON'T FEEL LIKE--

23:17.233 --> 23:19.767
I FEEL NAUSEOUS
AND LIKE I'M DRUGGED
OR SOMETHING.

23:19.800 --> 23:22.267
AND AS FAR AS
WHAT HAPPENED EARLIER,

23:22.300 --> 23:25.267
I'M MEAN,
YOU KNOW, USUALLY LIKE,
FIVE-MISSISSIPPI.

23:25.300 --> 23:27.733
HONEST TO GOD,
FIVE-MISSISSIPPI--
( claps )

23:28.767 --> 23:30.633
THAT'S ALL I NEED.

23:30.667 --> 23:32.967
WHY DON'T YOU JUST GO?

23:38.867 --> 23:41.133
WELL...
GOOD NIGHT.

24:04.133 --> 24:06.467
UGH!

24:29.400 --> 24:31.800
( orchestra playing )

25:06.067 --> 25:07.867
( sighs )

25:09.367 --> 25:11.967
( Jeff snoring )

25:15.100 --> 25:17.133
Leon:
AHHH!

25:17.167 --> 25:20.167
SOMEBODY GO IN THERE
AND PUT A SOCK IN THAT
MOTHERFUCKER'S MOUTH!

25:20.200 --> 25:21.967
( knocks at door )

25:22.067 --> 25:23.867
( moaning )

25:23.900 --> 25:25.800
( knocks )

25:25.833 --> 25:27.800
ONE SECOND!

25:29.533 --> 25:31.500
( door-knocker rapping )

25:34.800 --> 25:37.133
HEY, L.D.

25:37.167 --> 25:39.200
- WHAT'S GOING ON?
- COME ON IN, IT'S COLD.

25:39.233 --> 25:41.533
- YOU'RE BACK?
- YEAH. COULDN'T SLEEP.

25:41.567 --> 25:43.733
JEFF'S SNORE?
MAN, I'M TELLING YOU,
THAT WAS AWFUL.

25:43.767 --> 25:45.867
WORSE THAN
THE DAMN HURRICANE.

25:45.900 --> 25:48.900
- I KNOW, IT'S TERRIBLE.
- KIDS NEED TO SLEEP HERE.
Y'ALL GO ON UP TO BED.

25:48.933 --> 25:50.433
- GOOD NIGHT, LARRY.
- GOOD NIGHT.

25:50.467 --> 25:52.267
- GOOD NIGHT, MOM.
- GOOD NIGHT, Y'ALL.

25:52.300 --> 25:56.067
TALK TO YOUR BOY, MAN.
SHIT, THAT MOTHERFUCKER
SWALLOWED A KAZOO.

25:56.067 --> 25:59.233
- RIDICULOUS.
ALL FUCKING NIGHT!
- YEAH.

26:00.967 --> 26:03.067
COME ON!

26:03.067 --> 26:05.067
IT'S SAFE.
IT'S SAFE.

26:05.100 --> 26:07.433
ONE-MISSISSIPPI,
TWO-MISSISSIPPI,

26:07.467 --> 26:10.067
THREE-MISSISSIPPI...

26:10.100 --> 26:12.367
Jeff:
MY OWN DAUGHTER LOCKS
HERSELF IN HER ROOM,

26:12.400 --> 26:14.833
WON'T COME OUT
WHENEVER I'M HOME.

26:14.867 --> 26:17.900
MY WIFE--
ONE OF THE MOST WARM,
LOVING PEOPLE

26:17.933 --> 26:19.067
YOU COULD EVER MEET--

26:19.067 --> 26:21.500
HAS TURNED INTO A WITCH.

26:21.533 --> 26:24.467
A WITCH!
'CAUSE I'M BALD.
IT'S CHANGED EVERYTHING.

26:24.500 --> 26:27.100
BEN STILLER
WON'T WORK WITH ME

26:27.133 --> 26:30.467
BECAUSE I'M BALD!
I MEAN, COME ON.

26:30.500 --> 26:33.200
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY MILLIONS
I'M LOSING BECAUSE OF THAT?

26:33.233 --> 26:34.900
MILLIONS I'M LOSING!

26:34.933 --> 26:37.467
ALL RIGHT, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT ELSE TO SAY. THANK YOU.

26:37.500 --> 26:40.067
ALL RIGHT, MR. GREENE.
I UNDERSTAND NOW WE'RE
GOING TO HEAR

26:40.100 --> 26:42.367
FROM MR. LARRY DAVID,

26:42.400 --> 26:45.867
WHO WILL TESTIFY
ON MR. GREENE'S BEHALF.
MR. DAVID?

26:45.900 --> 26:48.133
- THANK YOU FOR BEING HERE.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

26:48.167 --> 26:50.467
MR. DAVID, AS YOU KNOW,
WE ARE LOOKING INTO

26:50.500 --> 26:52.867
ALLEGATIONS
OF PHYSICIAN MISCONDUCT

26:52.900 --> 26:55.100
STEMMING
FROM THE INCIDENT

26:55.133 --> 26:56.967
ON THE 17th
OF THIS MONTH.

26:57.067 --> 26:59.500
WOULD YOU PLEASE TELL
THE BOARD WHAT HAPPENED?

26:59.533 --> 27:02.367
I WAS HAVING LUNCH
IN THE CAFETERIA,

27:02.400 --> 27:05.567
AND I EXCUSED MYSELF
TO GO TO THE BATHROOM.

27:05.600 --> 27:09.333
YOU KNOW, IT'S--
IT'S A THING WE ALL DO.

27:09.367 --> 27:11.333
IT'S NOT A CRIME, RIGHT?

27:11.367 --> 27:14.167
- DON'T HAVE
TO BE EMBARRASSED.
- NO NEED FOR EMBARRASSMENT.

27:14.200 --> 27:15.533
GO AHEAD.

27:15.567 --> 27:17.233
ANYWAY, I WENT
INTO THE STALL.

27:17.267 --> 27:20.400
GENERALLY, WHEN I--
WHEN I USE A PUBLIC TOILET,

27:20.433 --> 27:23.067
I'LL-- I'LL GO INTO THE STALL
AS OPPOSED TO THE URINALS.

27:23.100 --> 27:25.667
I FIND THERE'S, YOU KNOW,
THERE'S NO PRIVACY.

27:25.700 --> 27:28.533
AND IF THERE'S NO DIVIDERS,
IT'S KIND OF LIKE GOING
IN A TROUGH.

27:28.567 --> 27:30.467
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
GO AHEAD, PLEASE.

27:30.500 --> 27:32.667
ANYWAY, SO I WENT
INTO THE STALL--

27:32.700 --> 27:35.367
I GUESS IT'S KIND
OF A HABIT NOW

27:35.400 --> 27:37.500
FOR ME TO GO
INTO THE STALL, IN A WAY.

27:37.533 --> 27:39.767
UM, IF IT'S OPEN,
IF IT'S AVAILABLE,

27:39.800 --> 27:41.600
I'LL-- I'LL GENERALLY
TAKE THE STALL.

27:41.633 --> 27:44.833
OF COURSE, WHAT YOU
FIND IN THERE IS-- YOU KNOW,
IS ANYBODY'S GUESS.

27:44.867 --> 27:47.233
ANYWAY,
SO I'M IN THE STALL,

27:47.267 --> 27:51.733
AND I OVERHEAR THIS GUY
TALKING ON HIS CELL PHONE.

27:51.767 --> 27:55.067
AND HE'S TALKING
TO A FRIEND OF HIS, AND
HE'S GETTING VERY UPSET

27:55.067 --> 27:57.067
'CAUSE HE HAD TO MOVE
SOME FURNITURE

27:57.067 --> 27:59.367
AND HE HURT HIS HAND.
AND HE-- AND HE'S SAYING,

27:59.400 --> 28:02.167
- "AND THEN I HURT MY HAND
'CAUSE THIS 300-LB--"
- ( door closes )

28:03.900 --> 28:05.700
SORRY I'M LATE.

28:05.733 --> 28:07.567
( man clears throat )

28:07.600 --> 28:10.400
PLEASE CONTINUE,
MR. DAVID.

28:10.433 --> 28:12.933
GO AHEAD, SIR.

28:12.967 --> 28:14.533
PLEASE CONTINUE.

28:16.867 --> 28:18.967
MR. DAVID,IS THERE A PROBLEM?

28:19.067 --> 28:23.067
PLEASE,
TELL US WHAT THE MAN
ON THE CELL PHONE SAID.

28:26.400 --> 28:29.067
MR. DAVID, TELL US
WHAT THE MAN SAID!

28:29.067 --> 28:31.700
- JUST SAY IT!
- YOU ARE WASTING THIS
COMMITTEE'S TIME.

28:31.733 --> 28:34.367
- LARRY, TELL 'EM.
- PLEASE TELL US WHAT
THE MAN SAID.

28:34.400 --> 28:36.267
- SAY IT!
- TELL 'EM!
WILL YOU TELL THEM?

28:36.300 --> 28:38.067
- JUST SAY IT!
- LARRY, JUST TELL 'EM!

28:38.100 --> 28:39.900
- TELL US WHAT THE MAN SAID!
- TELL THEM, PLEASE?

28:39.933 --> 28:42.200
- JUST DO IT, LARRY!
- TELL US NOW, MR. DAVID!

28:42.233 --> 28:44.900
- JUST SAY IT!
- LARRY, TELL 'EM!

28:44.933 --> 28:54.967
( theme music playing )

28:54.967 --> 29:05.067
( theme music playing )
